data.subject: Extended Save Image for ComfyUI
data.question: What additional image formats does the Extended Save Image custom node support?
data.answer: The Extended Save Image custom node supports saving images in JPEG and WEBP formats.

data.subject: Extended Save Image for ComfyUI
data.question: Does the Extended Save Image custom node support lossless and lossy compression for WEBP images?
data.answer: Yes, it supports both lossless and lossy compression for WEBP images.

data.subject: Extended Save Image for ComfyUI
data.question: How can I install the Extended Save Image custom node?
data.answer: Clone the repository into the `ComfyUI/custom_nodes` folder with `git clone https://github.com/palant/extended-saveimage-comfyui` and restart ComfyUI.

data.subject: Extended Save Image for ComfyUI
data.question: Can the resulting images from the Extended Save Image custom node be used to load a workflow?
data.answer: Yes, the resulting images from the Extended Save Image custom node can be used to load a workflow.

data.subject: Extended Save Image for ComfyUI
data.question: Does the Extended Save Image custom node embed metadata in the images?
data.answer: Yes, metadata is embedded in the images as usual.
